676	34	7	f	f	t	t	f	"[\\"True\\",\\"True\\",\\"True\\",\\"False\\",\\"True\\",\\"True\\",\\"True\\",\\"False\\",\\"True\\",\\"True\\",\\"​Implementation of User-Centered Design (UCD) focuses on creating interfaces that prioritize the user's needs, limitations, and behaviors. Based on the material covered:\\\\n​Consistency and Standards: Apps must use uniform icons and layouts so users don't have to relearn functions.\\\\n​Cognitive Load: Design should favor \\\\\\"Recognition over Recall\\\\\\" by making information visible rather than forcing memorization.\\\\n​Error Prevention: Critical or destructive actions should be visually distinct to prevent accidental user slips.\\\\n​Visual Hierarchy & Accessibility: Proper use of whitespace and high-contrast colors ensures that content is readable and easy to navigate for all users.\\"]"	87		2026-02-25 06:33:29.27	2026-03-01 13:39:39.509	0		2026-02-25 06:33:29.944	2026-03-01 13:39:40.118	"[]"
